When running the following program, it will print FAILED, though it should have 
succeeded.

public class X  {

    public static void main(String args[]) {
		boolean b = true;
		b = b && false;                 
		if (b) {
			System.out.println("FAILED");
		} else {
			System.out.println("SUCCESS");
		}
    }
