Quoting John: The recently released changes in runtime are causing many resources plugin tests to fail. There were two lines in the old code (InternalPlatform.setupMetaArea) that did this:
//try infer the device if there isn't one (windows) if (location.getDevice()==null) location = new Path(location.toFile().getAbsolutePath());
It looks like this code was lost in the refactoring to support platforms without a data area. If you don't do this, and you specify a "-data" area without a device, then there are many places where location comparisons fail to match because sometimes there is a device and sometimes there isn't. This sequence needs to be added back, in some central place when the location is being initialized, to be sure that it always has a device.

